qas.question: What percentage of people voted on March 26?
How many constituencies had run-off elections?
How many CPSU endorsement having candidates lost to independents?

context: In the March 26 general elections, voter participation was an impressive <a0_0>89.8%<a0_0/>, and 1,958 (including 1,225 district seats) of the 2,250 CPD seats were filled. In district races, run-off elections were held in <a1_0>76<a1_0/> constituencies on April 2 and 9 and fresh elections were organized on April 20 and 14 to May 23, in the 199 remaining constituencies where the required absolute majority was not attained. While most CPSU-endorsed candidates were elected, <a2_0>more than 300<a2_0/> lost to independent candidates such as Yeltsin, physicist Andrei Sakharov and lawyer Anatoly Sobchak.
